izing the project structure. I'm thinking through the remaining config files now. For the API response handling, I need to decide between a simple POST request, Server-Sent Events for streaming progress updates, or WebSocket—SSE seems like the best balance for showing real-time analysis progress without too much complexity, though a polling approach could work too if I want to keep things simpler.\n\nActually, I'll use Next.js's streaming API with ReadableStream to send chunks of data as the analysis progresses, which gives me the responsiveness I want without extra complexity.\n\nSetting up the streaming response...\n\nWriting the frontend handler... Writing package.json and dependencies... I need to verify the latest versions for the key dependencies—Next.js 15.x, @langchain/langgraph 0.2.x, and @google/generative-ai 0.21.x should work well. Now I'm setting up the LangGraph workflow using the annotation-based state system, defining the state schema with video properties and creating nodes for the researcher and critic agents that will process and evaluate the video content. Defining the state annotation...\n\nI'm setting up the root annotation with all the fields I need for the workflow—video input, researcher findings, validated issues, overall assessment, and error handling. I'm going with the simplest Annotation syntax and can adjust if needed based on how the SDK actually behaves when we run it.\n\nNow I'm deciding between using the LangChain wrapper for Google's model versus the native SDK directly. The native `@google/generative-ai` definitely supports video file URIs, but I'm less certain about the LangChain wrapper's capabilities there. I'll stick with the native SDK for the actual model calls to ensure video handling works smoothly, while keeping LangGraph for the workflow orchestration.\n\nBefore I start writing code, let me clarify how the Gemini Files API actually works: I upload a file using the file manager, which returns a response with the file name and URI, then I need to poll until the file reaches an ACTIVE state, and finally I can reference it in model calls using the file URI and MIME type. The upload method expects a file path as a string rather than a buffer. I should ask the user for the latest documentation before I start writing code, so I don't end up having to refactor everything later.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":277,"cache_read_input_tokens":18149,"output_tokens":9981,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":277,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":3,"output_tokens":9981,"cache_read_input_tokens":18149,"cache_creation_input_tokens":277,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":277},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CaJhXJ5VCCPDQP9gXKhsT","type":"assistant","uuid":"101314b5-20f3-40ec-8790-791508ce17fb","timestamp":"2026-04-22T11:06:45.387Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"/home/akshay/projects/video_ux_analyzer","sessionId":"43aa6f4e-238a-49ff-bcee-676bf9b5ead2","version":"2.1.111","gitBranch":"HEAD"}
{"parentUuid":"101314b5-20f3-40ec-8790-791508ce17fb","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_012Y6JhhcSEp2DDUVc95r2uM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good architecture choice. Before I start writing code, I need to verify two APIs to avoid writing stale code:\n\n1. **`@google/generative-ai` Files API** — specifically, how to upload a video buffer/stream server-side (not from a file path), and the exact method to reference it in a model call with `gemini-3-flash-preview`\n\n2. **`@langchain/langgraph`** — the current `Annotation.Root` / `StateGraph` API for defining state and nodes (the 0.2.x API changed significantly from 0.1.x)\n\nCan you run these through your internet LLM? I want to make sure I use the right method signatures for:\n- Gemini file upload from a Node.js `Buffer` + polling for `ACTIVE` state\n- LangGraph state annotation + node return type (e.g., `Partial<State>` vs `Command`)"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":277,"cache_read_input_tokens":18149,"output_tokens":9981,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":277,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":3,"output_tokens":9981,"cache_read_input_tokens":18149,"cache_creation_input_tokens":277,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":277},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CaJhXJ5VCCPDQP9gXKhsT","type":"assistant","uuid":"153c189b-58ad-4e37-9ed6-898da665cf58","timestamp":"2026-04-22T11:06:47.780Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"/home/akshay/projects/video_ux_analyzer","sessionId":"43aa6f4e-238a-49ff-bcee-676bf9b5ead2","version":"2.1.111","gitBranch":"HEAD"}
