{"parentUuid":"d9b9478c-8413-4d5f-b192-2e3b0b716424","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01WUfomaTDhGhwP6yBijBgMY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user has two things going on:\n\n1. There's an \"Analysis failed\" error: `[GoogleGenerativeAI Error]: Error fetching from https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/upload/v1beta/files: fetch failed`\n\n2. They want to add a feature: timestamp-based video sync where clicking a timestamp in the issue cards jumps the video to that exact moment.\n\nLet me address both:\n\n**Error fix first:**\nThe error is from `fileManager.uploadFile` failing. The `fetch failed` error typically means a network issue or the API endpoint is wrong. But looking at the gemini.ts code, we're writing to a temp file and uploading. The error could be:\n\n\n- The buffer size is too large to write\n- Network connectivity issue\n- The temp file path issue\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the error: `Error fetching from https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/upload/v1beta/files: fetch failed` - this is a network-level error, not an auth error. It means the `fetch` call itself failed. This could be the Node.js environment in Next.js not handling large file uploads properly, the upload timing out, or the buffer being passed incorrectly to the API. I'm also noticing the model was switched to `gemini-2.5-flash` from a previous version, which might have different upload requirements.\n\nThe `fetch failed` error is likely related to how Node.js handles large multipart form data uploads through the Google AI package. The temp file approach should theoretically work since the file manager reads the path and uploads it, but the network-level failure suggests either a body size limit in Next.js truncating the video, or possibly just a transient network issue.\n\nLet me shift focus to the timestamp sync feature the user mentioned, since this network error might resolve itself. The core idea is to sync timestamps between the video playback and the transcript data.\n\nSetting up the sync mechanism... Implementing the timestamp parsing and wiring up the seek functionality across components. I need to make sure `videoRef` flows from the page down through `VideoUploader` to `AnalysisResults`, and then the timestamp clicks can trigger seeking. I could also add a brief highlight effect on the issue card when clicked for better visual feedback.\n\nThe network error with the Gemini Files API upload might be related to how Next.js handles large FormData bodies in memory, or possibly a network connectivity issue in the deployment environment, but since we're moving forward with the feature implementation, I'll focus on getting the seek-to-timestamp functionality working first. Writing component props and handlers... Still writing the timestamp button... Writing the component updates...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":58255,"cache_read_input_tokens":10584,"output_tokens":2509,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":58255,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":3,"output_tokens":2509,"cache_read_input_tokens":10584,"cache_creation_input_tokens":58255,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":58255},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CaNa3cfbvT82AimHb9gDx","type":"assistant","uuid":"69087f5c-ec7d-4246-926b-81accf95123d","timestamp":"2026-04-24T12:09:37.806Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"/home/akshay/projects/video_ux_analyzer","sessionId":"43aa6f4e-238a-49ff-bcee-676bf9b5ead2","version":"2.1.118","gitBranch":"HEAD"}
