tepper** — white card, rounded check for done, ring-pulse for active\n\n**Jira modal touchups:** Replaced all dark-mode `/15` tints with light pastel `-50 / -700 / -200`.\n\n---\n\n## 9. Card Layout Fix (Empty Vertical Space)\n\n**User:** Sent screenshot of a card showing the icon column was vertically empty below the icon. Pointed out the reference doesn't have this — content flows naturally below the icon.\n\n**Assistant:** Restructured both `ValidatedCard` and `SkeletonCard`:\n- **Header row** (icon + category pill + severity pill + verdict pill) at the top using `items-center`\n- **Body** (description, timestamp, critic quote) full-width below — no longer indented under the icon column\n- **Footer** (Create Jira Ticket) below body with border separator\n\nThe icon now visually anchors only the header, and the body breathes across the full card width — Twisty's actual pattern.\n\n---\n\n## 10. .gitignore + Git Staging\n\n**User:** \"Write proper gitignore\"\n\n**Assistant:** Replaced the one-line `node_modules` gitignore with a comprehensive Next.js gitignore covering: dependencies, build artifacts (`.next/`, `out/`), env files (preserving `.env.local.example`), logs, deployment metadata (Vercel/Netlify), IDE/editor junk, OS files, caches (`.turbo`, `.eslintcache`), stray media files (`*.mp4`/`.mov`/`.webm`), competing lockfiles (yarn/pnpm/bun).\n\n**User:** \"Unstage all changes and then git add .\"\n\n**Assistant:** Ran `git rm -r --cached .` to clear the index (325 files including `.next/` build output that had been committed before the .gitignore was applied), then `git add .` which respected the new ignore rules. Result: 29 staged files, no `.next/`, no `node_modules/`, no `tsconfig.tsbuildinfo`.\n\n---\n\n## 11. README\n\n**User:** Provided three links and asked: \"Mention them at the top in the README file and write clear instructions on setup and explanation of project.\"\n\nLinks:\n- Loom Part 1 (UI walkthrough)\n- Loom Part 2 (architecture deep-dive)\n-